name: Blue State Coffee
comment: This place is exactly what you'd expect it to be, from its name.

name: Cafe' Verde, Fair Trade Coffee Bar
directions: On 4th Ave, between Ann and Catherine.  In Kerrytown, across from the Farmers Market and Aut Bar.  Rest rooms are on the ground floor
comment: Cafe Verde is part of the People's Food Co-op.  Serves only certified fair trade coffee and tea.  Food options include vegan and gluten-free. Co-op membership not required to shop -all are welcome!

name: Fuel Coffee Shop
directions: Walk in past the main counter and turn to the right to walk through the doorway to the bathroom.
comment: you probably should buy something... but i feel like you could easily sneak in!

name: U of I Library Main Stacks
directions: There are single-user gender-neutral bathrooms on all 8 floors of the eastern half of the stacks.  Get there by going to the 2nd floor of the library, going past the circulation desk, and showing your I-Card.

name: Bakersfield College, FACE building
directions: Near the Renegade Room

name: Library Science Building
directions: It's in the basement, just outside the Center for Children's Books.  If you come in the front door, there's a staircase on your right that will take you right there.
comment: The building closes in the evenings and on weekends, and only GSLIS students/staff can swipe in.

name: South Riverdale Community Health Centre
directions: Building is at SE corner of Queen & Carlaw.  Go up to the 2nd floor (elevator or stairs), turn right.  The 1st floor has gendered bathrooms.  Note: 2nd floor is open to the public, it's where the main clinic is.
comment: The bathroom has a baby changing station!

name: Shopping Center Vida Bella
comment: On the second floor in a mall are two bathrooms (male and female) both have toilet paper.Hours: Monday to Friday: 09:00 am to 20hs.Saturdays: 09:00 am to 19:00 pm without closing at noon.

name: Walmart
directions: In the very back of the store in the photo lab. There is a locking "family restroom" in between men/women restrooms.
comment: It can be a little awkward going in because all the employees go through the doors nearby to get to the back rooms of the store, but nobody really pays attention.

name: NCNM Main Building
directions: The genderfree bathroom is located on the 2nd Floor of building. The building is shaped like the letter H, and the genderfree bathroom is in the connector part of the H.  Take a stairwell (or elevator) up one flight to 2nd floor. Go to the middle hallway on 2nd floor.  The bathroom is halfway down that middle hallway.
comment: NCNM (National College of Natural Medicine) is a school.  It is opened Monday - Friday, typical business hours, and sometimes on the weekends.

name: Midway Cafe
directions: Unisex, one-unit, locking bathroom.  When you walk in the door, the bathrooms are across the room against the opposite wall-just beyond the stage.  Or, if you're facing the stage, just to the left of the stage.
comment: This is a dive bar and is open at approx. 2pm every day and closes at 2am every night.  There is sometimes a cover after 8pm.  Also Midway hosts Queeraoke every Thursday nights and Plastique (queer dance night) monthly Sundays. They also have other 'queer'/non gender-conforming events monthly, as well as   Occasional Original Plumbing events.

name: Silver Spur Bar
directions: Near back, past pool table on the right. Or enter back door from parking lot accessed on 20th Avenue.
comment: Rainbow flag 'pin' sticker on wall, saw an old lesbian couple celebrating their marriage there years ago. Nice clean dive bar.

name: Wal-Mart
directions: The family restroom in the back past electtronics

name: Johnson & Wales University Intercultural Center
directions: Turn right as you enter building, straight ahead on the right just past the kitchenette.
comment: 8:00 AM - 8:00 PM, Monday -Thursday; 8:00 AM - 4:00 PM, Friday. Stay and watch TV or socialize!

name: Coffee & Crepes
comment: Mon-Thu 7AM - 9PMFri-Sat 7AM - 10:30PMSun 9AM - 8PMStaff is friendly.

name: Randy's Pizza RTP
directions: There are two sets of restrooms. The ones on the right side of the restaurant near the counter are gendered. The restroom behind the larger dinning area on the left side is a single stall and genderfree.
comment: Friendly staff. Okay food. M-F 10:30 A - 8 P. Sat. Noon - 8 PM.

name: Morrisville Deli
directions: Unisex restroom is in the back to the left of the soda fountain.
comment: There is only one bathroom, it is unisex. Not sure if it counts as accessible or not. It is a larger size but I don't think there were any bars.Their hours are a bit short 8a - 4pm ( 3pm ) on Sundays. The food is pretty good, especially if you like NY style deli's.

name: Health Initiatives for Youth (HIFY)
directions: HIFY is a non-profit youth organization and if you ring the bell (the door is usually) locked someone should let you in. The bathroom is on the 2nd floor.

name: Kettering University Campus Center
directions: There are two gender neutral bathrooms just inside the main entrance of the Campus Center.
comment: They are the only publicly accessible gender neutral bathrooms in the entire campus. There may be some in Thompson Hall, but bathroom signs there basically change weekly.

name: BSC
directions: Walk down the stairs. It's south past ABP. Look for the bathroom sign. It's in-between the gendered bathrooms.

name: Pound Hall, Harvard Law School
directions: First floor
comment: Several bathrooms included one labeled "Gender Neutral."

name: Rebel
comment: Friday Sept 16th 9pm-3am

name: Flying Star Restaurant
directions: all of the Flying Stars have gender neutral restrooms. You just walk in. They probably prefer you buy something but you don't have to.

name: albuquerque, New Mexico, Cottonwood Mall
directions: near food court
comment: its a gender neutral family bathroom. One single room. The mall is free to enter.

name: MCC Windsor/Westminster United Church
directions: One on main floor to left (around the corner) of entrance (very small and not accessible); second is down main hall (during office hours you must be let in) through social room to the right (large; wheelchair accessible through sanctuary; two low steps; grab bars)
comment: Church office hours T - F 9 - 3; also open Sundays most of the day

name: BevMo!
directions: Back right corner of the store, just past the beer cooler.
comment: Legally, people under the age of 21 must be accompanied by someone over 21 while in the store, but we don't check IDs at the door. If you're under 21, just ask the cashier if you can use the bathroom and you shouldn't have an issue. The bathrooms do not need keys.We'd really like it if you bought something (we have COLD Mexican Cokes!), but we understand that the need to safely pee should be free.

name: Windsor Pride Community Centre
directions: Accessible from the main room

name: Urban Bean
directions: Go straight to the back.

name: Internationalist Books and Community Center
comment: 11-8 monday through saturday 12-6 sunday. Radical bookstore and community center

name: The Loft Literary Center
directions: 2nd and 3rd floors
comment: Mon-Sat 8am-8pm, Sun 10am-5pm

name: ghana,banker
directions: nice good looking person always happy and friendly,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
comment: nice good looking person always happy and friendly,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,

name: Altamont Free Library
directions: Library is in basement of bank building, access through bank door. Go down stairs, bathroom is directly in front of you.
comment: At some time in future, library will move across street to historic train station.

name: Bulimia Anorexia Nervosa Association
directions: 4th floor, first door left of elevators.
comment: If locked ask either business on the floor for the key. Open 9am-5pm, M-F

name: New Pioneer Food Co-op
street: 22 S. Van Buren St. Iowa City, Iowa
directions: In the back area between the dairy and the meat aisle. Two separate bathrooms, one larger than the other (not sure if accessible, sorry).

name: Rite Aid
directions: In the back near the pharmacy. You can stroll right in, but you probably should not tell them you are only there to use the bathroom.
comment: Not sure of the exact street address but its right next to CVS which is 12 W. Independence St.

name: Wendy's
directions: Turn right after you walk in the main doors and go straight back

name: Ming Guan
directions: To the left in the back, single locking genderfree bathroom

name: Starbucks
directions: Two formerly gendered bathrooms, now both are unisex.
comment: When busy, there is a line.

name: Baroli Cafe
directions: Main floor entrance in front of Sears between Dundas/Queen, from Yonge St.
comment: I felt I had to buy a coffee to use it.

name: Mike's Pizza
directions: Go straight in. There is a hallway on the right. It winds a bit, but at the end there are two (roomy) bathrooms. They are gendered but there is rarely a line and they are singles.

name: "Rush Center"
directions: Shares the building with several other businesses, go in the main entrance Rush Center door is on the left of the hall.
comment: Generally open 9-5, may have access at night and on weekends depending on if an event is being held in the space.

name: Roger Clapp Greenhouses
directions: Enter through front door, bathroom will be down the hall on the left.

name: UMaine Memorial Union
directions: Take stairs down; bathroom is in hallway near University Credit Union and Wade Student Center.

name: Giacomo
directions: Back of dining room

name: L'Escalier
directions: Right beside the kitchen.Juste à côté de la cuisine.
comment: 2 single stall bathrooms face to face.  Non-identified with genders, but usually men tend to use the one facing the front of the bistro and women, the one facing the kitchen.2 salles de bain individuelles qui se font face.  Aucune n'est identifiée mais les hommes ont tendance à utiliser celle qui fait face au devant du bistro et les femmes, elles, celle qui fait face à la cuisine.

name: Olco
directions: Right in the back of the store. (The dep is si small, you should not miss it!)À l'arrière du magasin.  (Le dépanneur est si petit, c'est immanquable!)
comment: Week : open at 5 a.m closes at 11 p.mWeekend : open at 7 a.m closes at 10 p.mClean, you have to ask for the key.  You don't really have to buy something, but be nice with the employees and it should more than ok,Semaine : ouvre à 5hr et ferme à 23hrFin de semaine : ouvre à 7hr et ferme à 22hrPropre, il faut demander la clé pour y accéder.  Vous n'avez pas vraiment besoin d'acheter quelque chose, mais s'il-vous-plaît, soyez gentils avec les employés et il ne devrait pas y avoir de problème.

name: Big Fresh
directions: Go to the back, take a right at the colorful curtains.
comment: Good falafel wrap!

name: Northwestern Michigan College
directions: Cafeteria/Bookstore building (used to be West Hall). Bathroom is a single use, locking, accessible bathroom labeled "Unisex". Located on the main floor just outside the cafeteria area.
comment: Note that you need a parking decal or to pay a meter to park at NMC. Alternatively you can park at the Grand Traverse County Civic Center free and it's about a 5 - 10 minute walk to this building on NMC's campus.

name: Joann Fabrics
directions: Back of store.
comment: This used to be the men's bathroom, but they have changed it into a genderfree, family accessible restroom. Contains a urinal, locking stall, baby change station and sink. The entire bathroom can be locked too so it can be a single use if desired.

name: Barone's
directions: Past the bar, make a right and then a left past the kitchen.
comment: This restaurant is across the street from the Oxwood Inn which hosts Club Shine, so they're probably used to seeing transgendered people. Still, walking in, this place feels pretty old-fashioned, so you might feel a bit nervous. Everyone seems very friendly though, and the food is delicious.

name: The Warehouse
directions: It's a vintage/local designer clothing store. Turn right at the entrance. Door will be in front of you near the corner with the close wall.
comment: Tues-Sun, 11am-8pmhttp://thewarehousela.com/(213) 975-0035

name: Drug Mart
directions: Gender neutral family restroom.  Take a right as you enter the store.  It's located in the front corner.

name: Grey Lodge Pub
directions: Upstairs, there are 2 gendered but single room bathrooms.
comment: Didn't use or see downstairs bathrooms.

name: Navarre Park
directions: Park is at foot of bridge out to Santa Rosa Island
comment: Multiple genderfree porta-potties, at least one accessible. Park hours 7 am-10 pm, but you can pull into the lot where these are anytime

name: Century Olympia Movie Theater, Westfield Capitol Mall
directions: The movie theater has a Family/unisex restroom to the left of the snack bar. You must be a movie theater patron to use the restroom.It is accessible and locks as a single-toilet restroom.
comment: I can now go to movies without worrying about having to "hold it" the whole time! Unlike some family restrooms this one is a single stall, locking restroom so you don't have to have a kid with you to use this restroom. It is for anyone with a need for a more accessible restroom.

name: Starbucks
directions: Down the hall on the left side
comment: Need to buy something and ask for the code.

name: Arlington Street Church
directions: Gender neutral single use bathroom upstairs, general use bathrooms downstairs.
comment: Sunday mornings 10:30-1

name: Hochschule fuer Bildende KÃÄÂ¼nste (HfBK)
directions: ThereÂ´s a huge genderfree toilet in the basement where the student cantine is.
comment: The HfBK is the university of fine arts in Hamburg. But if itÂ´s open (only in daytimes) you can just walk in, nobody cares and the toilets are genderfree on every floor. ThereÂ´s also pretty good cheap food in the cantine and also there nobody cares if youÂ´re studying.

name: Dunkin Donuts
comment: This bathroom was impressively clean for a chain coffee shop bathroom.

name: Trader Joe's
directions: It's in the back of the store. There are two genderfree restrooms.

name: Skagit Valley Food Co-Op
directions: There are three bathrooms. Two on the 1st floor and one on the second floor. On the first floor there is a single bathroom by the cash registers and a bathroom back by the produce.Upstairs there is a bathroom by the merch room.

name: Comstock Saloon
directions: 1st floor, back of the bar on the lower side (behind the booths)

name: Georgia Southern University
directions: Inside the Counseling Center - kindly ask the secretary for directions to the staff restrooms - which are single stall and genderfree
comment: 8am-5pm Monday-Friday

name: Green
directions: behind the restaurant, you can enter from the parking lot so even if you don't eat their vegan deliciousness you can pee safely
comment: they also have good food

name: North Bowl
directions: Upstairs, a ton of gender neutral single room bathrooms.
comment: Did not use or see downstairs bathrooms.

name: Uno's
comment: Ask about beer specials and the "snack" menu!

name: Mars Bar
directions: At the back.

name: Merced Lofts
directions: Either walk around or through one of the businesses to the back of the building. Both the comic shop and coffee shop are passthrough. Ask for a key.
comment: Usually clean enough. Changing station in the first one.

name: Books & Company
directions: First floor, near the back patio door.
comment: Bathrooms have specific "colour schemes" and used to be gendered, but are now genderfree as far as I know.

name: 3rd Ave Collective
directions: Walk straight in, to the back, and on the right.
comment: Hours: Noon-6.Awesome little info-shop - check out some books and zines while you're there!

name: Rose 32 Bread/Bakery
directions: Right as you enter the side (main) door from the parking lot.  It is immediately on your right.  It has a label that goes with the lock so it will say "vacant" if the door is unlocked.
comment: Hours:  Wed-Fri 6 am to 5 pm, Sat-Sun 7 am to 3 pm.  Very nice single bathroom with lock.  ANd great baked goods and coffee.

name: USF Tampa Library
directions: All 6 floors have a gender free/handicap bathroom that is single stall/locking door. Located in lobby on each floor across from elevators.
comment: If you're not a student, you do have to pay for parking, but if you're just coming in to pee you might be able to get out fast enough to avoid a ticket.-Park in loading zone and you won't get ticketed. 12-7am - only folks with vaild USF IDs allowed in library

name: Escafe
directions: Walk into the bar and go straight to the back
comment: Bathrooms are labeled 'Either' and 'Or'

name: Linn's of Cambria
directions: To the left of the bakery

name: I heart yogurt
directions: From the entrance, walk straight ahead to the back of the store and it's right there on the left.
comment: Very clean, very friendly people.  Hours are 11 am to 11 pm every day.

name: Hot Doug's
directions: Near the counter.
comment: Very funny signs. The men's signhas a a picture of a weiner in a bun while the women's sign has just the bun.

name: Vi-kings Bar
directions: In the Back

name: Starbucks Coffee City Hall
directions: Back and to the left
comment: You'll probably need to ask for a key, but you don't have to buy a thing.

name: Hard Rock Cafe DC
directions: Opposite end of stairs, the one marked "Private".

name: Naco - Gallery & Cafe
directions: When you walk in, head straight to the stairs.  The bathrooms are down a few steps, turn right, and then down into the basement.
comment: It's a small place, and they hold dance parties for gay men, so generally pretty queer-friendly.

name: Village Inn
directions: On the north side of the restaurant, near the entry to the kitchen.
comment: Three restrooms available: Men, Women, Unisex.

name: Upper Limits Climbing Gym
directions: in the back, near the lockers, stairs and vending machines
comment: they have two neutral, single, locking bathrooms even one neutral, locking shower (I love this place)
